### Admin API Testing
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/admin
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Admin Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "adminPassword123"
}

### 2. Get Admin Profile (requires JWT token from login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.jwt}}

### 3. Update Admin Profile - Email Only
PUT {{baseUrl}}/profile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.jwt}}

{
  "email": "newemail@example.com"
}

### 4. Update Admin Profile - Email and Password
PUT {{baseUrl}}/profile
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.jwt}}

{
  "email": "newemail@example.com",
  "currentPassword": "adminPassword123",
  "newPassword": "newPassword123",
  "confirmPassword": "newPassword123"
}

### 5. Change Admin Password
PUT {{baseUrl}}/change-password
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.jwt}}

{
  "currentPassword": "adminPassword123",
  "newPassword": "newPassword123",
  "confirmPassword": "newPassword123"
}

### 6. Check if Email Exists
GET {{baseUrl}}/email-exists?email=admin@example.com

### 7. Test Invalid Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "invalid@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### 8. Test Invalid Email Format
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "adminPassword123"
}

### 9. Test Password Mismatch
PUT {{baseUrl}}/change-password
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{$auth.jwt}}

{
  "currentPassword": "adminPassword123",
  "newPassword": "newPassword123",
  "confirmPassword": "differentPassword123"
}

### 10. Test Unauthorized Access (no token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/profile
